@node "9." "How do I Install this to Maxs?"
 This bit was sent to me by Steve Bowman. This is how he has it setup on his
BBS, so it should work on others too.

To run this door you'll need the MaxShell utility which is available from the
Aminet and most Maxs BBS's.

First you need to write a script to run CD Reader. This script should be in
your doors:maxshell/ directory.

This is how I have it set up on my system......

cd doors:cdreader/ maxs_cdreader "%f" 9 endcli

%f should be known to all but for completeness it passes the username to the
called program.

9 is to signify how many files you'll allow your users to tag at any given
time. Max limit 32678 ;)

Then you'll need to set up the menu option to run the door on whatever menu
you want it to be run from. The line in your menu config should look something
like this:

KEY  FUNCTION  EXTRA  LO ACC  HI ACC  FILENAME/NAME/DEST/PATH:

 ?      34       0      ??      ??    ms:maxshell cdr-startup -c -d -t

(Assuming you have doors:maxshell/ assigned as ms: and your script is called
CDR-startup.)

You`ll also need a key which will run the Autosend door, as the CD Reader door
copies the tagged files to the user's autosend directory. You could set this
up as something like "Download tagged files from CD-ROMs". The line in your
menu config should look something like this:

KEY  FUNCTION  EXTRA  LO ACC  HI ACC  FILENAME/NAME/DEST/PATH:

 ?      34       0      ??      ??    doors:autosend +

(Don`t forget the + at the end of the path.)

@endnode

